The paper discusses graph embedding, which is a topic related to machine learning and data science. The proposed framework for comparing embeddings is likely to be of interest to researchers in the field of machine learning, specifically those working on graph-based methods. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of embeddings for compressing and representing networks, which could fall under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of selecting the best embedding, which could fall under the categories of cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for evaluating embeddings, which could fall under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
